cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR

This paper is about Complex Word Identification (CWI), which is a task related to natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and machine learning, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of features and the selection of models, which are common topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses inconsistencies in the annotation of the data, which suggests that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) could also be a relevant category.
